I'm happy to help, but it seems like the source text is incomplete. However, I'll provide a translation of what's available.  "Salut Cllaude271,"
To have gone through the state you describe (after a mix of gossips, micropoints, taz, keta, in short everything that passed through there),
If I can give you a piece of advice, it's just to tell you that it's all just psychological.
The more you take it to heart, the worse it will get.
A very simple thing in these cases, you take deep breaths, you breathe softly, and you lean into a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes, sometimes you might feel like they're closing in on you).
After several months of use, especially when mixing, you can still experience effects, especially after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Claude532 said, consulting a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of those voices that clutter your head.
Keep fishing, and stay positive.
